Athletics doping: Russia not welcome after Wada report - Steve Cram
Media playback is not supported on this deviceBBC commentator and former world 1500m champion Steve Cram says Russia should be told they are no longer welcome in athletics until they "can get their house in order".AWorld Anti-Doping Agency's independent commissionexamined allegations of doping, cover-ups, and extortion in Russian athletics, which also implicated the IAAF, the sport's world governing body.Cram says "we are all to blame" for allowing people "not up to scratch" to get into powerful positions in world sport, but believes that IAAF president Lord Coe is the man to enact change within athletics.